snippet.title: My Hair care routine || Niha Sisters || My Hair growth journey ||
snippet.description:
Haircare Routine : Step-by-Step Guide

1. Oil Massage Before Shampooing :
Regular oiling nourishes the scalp, reduces dryness, strengthens hair follicles, and adds shine over time. Always massage your scalp gently to promote better blood circulation.

2. Essential Oil Addition :
Mix 3 drops of essential oil like rosemary with your carrier oil to boost hair growth. Additionally, after every wash, spray rosemary water on your scalp for improved results.

3. Use Mild Shampoos and Conditioners :
Choose mild shampoos instead of harsh, chemical-laden products. Always condition your hair after every wash, especially if you have frizzy hair. Otherwise, condition at least twice a week. Try reverse conditioning (conditioning before shampoo) twice a month for extra nourishment.

4. Weekly Hair Mask Routine :
Apply a mild or homemade hair mask once a week to deeply condition and hydrate your hair. Regular use improves texture, adds shine, and reduces frizz and breakage.

5. Use Lukewarm or Cool Water :
Always rinse your hair with lukewarm or cool water. Hot water strips away natural oils, making hair dry and more prone to breakage.

6. Gentle Shampooing Technique :
Avoid rubbing the scalp harshly. Apply an adequate amount of shampoo and gently massage with your fingertips or a hair massaging tool. When rinsing, carefully squeeze out excess water without twisting or pulling the hair.

7. Scalp Care :
Maintaining a clean, healthy scalp promotes better hair growth. Exfoliate the scalp gently and keep it moisturized. Wash your hair 2–3 times a week.

8. Switch to Microfiber Towels :
Replace regular towels with microfiber towels. They are softer and much gentler on both hair and scalp, reducing friction and breakage.

9. Hair Serum Application : 
Hair serum plays a vital role during the hair growth journey. It locks in moisture and smooths frizz. Always apply serum on damp or towel-dried hair, not dry hair.

10. Avoid Heat Styling Tools :
Minimize or completely avoid heat styling tools like dryers, straighteners, and curlers. If you must use them, always apply a heat protectant spray to shield your hair from damage.

11. Sleep on Satin Pillowcases : 
Sleeping on satin pillowcases reduces friction, prevents frizz, and is much gentler on your hair. If possible, sleep without pillows for better blood circulation, but ensure you are still resting on a satin surface.

12. Cover Your Hair When Going Out :
Shield your hair from dust, pollution, and UV rays by covering it with a scarf, bandana, or using a silk-lined cap under helmets. Alternatively, opt for loose buns or braids instead of leaving your hair open.

13. Tie Hair in a Braid or Loose Bun :
Tying hair in a loose braid or bun helps minimize friction and breakage compared to tighter hairstyles like ponytails.

14. Switch to a Wooden Comb :
Use a wooden comb instead of plastic. Wooden combs help reduce static, distribute natural oils evenly, enhance shine, and are gentler, minimizing hair breakage.

15. Night Haircare Routine :
Before sleeping, gently comb your hair with a wooden comb and secure it in a protective hairstyle (like a loose braid). Sleep on a satin pillowcase for added protection.

16. Focus on Food Intake :
Nutrition is crucial. Consume protein and iron-rich foods like boiled eggs (once or twice a day), green vegetables, and fruits. Monitor your iron levels, as iron deficiency can cause hair fall. Additionally, soak almonds overnight, drink the water, and eat the soaked almonds the next morning for great results.

17. Choose the Right Haircut :
Haircuts play an important role. For volume and bounce, basic U-cuts and straight cuts work well, especially for thinning hair. Avoid layers, feathers, or V-cuts if you’re experiencing hair fall. Regularly trim split ends to support healthy hair growth.

18. Be Cautious with Hair Treatments :
Research thoroughly before opting for any hair treatments. Personally, treatments like keratin caused damage rather than improvements. Stick to natural methods unless absolutely necessary.


---

Important Final Note:

Patience is key. Visible results like baby hairs may take 3–6 months.

Initial hair fall is normal when introducing rosemary, but it should gradually decrease over time.

Monitor your hair: If excessive hair fall persists after 1–1.5 months, reconsider the products you're using, as they might not be suitable for you.

In Ghum Hai Kisikey Pyaar Meiin, the character Savi is introduced as Sai and Virat’s daughter. Savi brings a new dimension to the story as she becomes a bridge and a source of emotional complexity between her estranged parents, Sai and Virat. Her presence challenges Virat's loyalty to his family and reignites unresolved feelings between him and Sai. Rajat is another recent character who brings twists to the plot, affecting the dynamics between the main characters and creating new conflicts. Both Savi and Rajat play pivotal roles in evolving the storyline, deepening the emotional layers of the show, and introducing new conflicts that keep the characters—and viewers—on their toes.

snippet.title: Dravid's Reaction on Vaibhav Suryavanshi Century: വൈഭവിനെ അഭിനന്ദിച്ച് ദ്രാവിഡ്
snippet.description:
പരിക്കേറ്റ് പുറത്തായ രാജസ്ഥാൻ റോയൽസ് ക്യാപ്റ്റൻ സഞ്ജു സാംസണിന് പകരം ഓപണറായി ഇറങ്ങി കിടിലൻ സെഞ്ചുറിക്കൊപ്പം റെക്കോഡുകളും വാരിക്കൂട്ടിയിരിക്കുകയാണ് വൈഭവ് സൂര്യവംശി. ഗുജറാത്ത് ടൈറ്റൻസിനെതിരെ കളത്തിലിറങ്ങിയ വൈഭവ്, ഐപിഎൽ ചരിത്രത്തിലെ ഏറ്റവും വേഗതയേറിയ രണ്ടാമത്തെ സെഞ്ചുറിയാണ് അടിച്ചുകൂട്ടിയത്.
#VaibhavSuryavanshiCentury
#VaibhavSuryavanshi #Suryavanshi 
#RahulDravid #RRVsGT #IPL2025

snippet.title: Pahalgam Attack | Pahalgam Hero Who Carried Injured Boy On His Back: 'Humanity Before Religion'
snippet.description:
The massive terror attack in Pahalgam, Jammu and Kashmir, while spreading shock and horror, also showed hope as multiple heroes stepped forward from among the locals. One such was Sajad Ahmed Bhatt. A video of him carrying a boy, injured when the terrorists opened fire on a group of tourists, killing 26 people, has been widely circulated. The video shows Mr Bhatt running downhill over the rocky terrain, his steps never faltering. The boy was on his back, clad in Mr Bhatt's orange jacket to keep him warm.

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | Barcelona 3-2 Real Madrid | Copa del Rey Final 2025
snippet.description:
Real Madrid were defeated in extra time in the final of the Copa del Rey. In a strong second half, Madrid came back from Pedri's goal in the 28th minute with a free-kick from Mbappé in the 70th minute and a header from Tchouameni seven minutes later. In the 84th minute, Ferran Torres scored to take the game into extra time, which was decided by Koundé in the 116th minute with a shot from the edge of the area.

es.title: RESUMEN | Barcelona 3-2 Real Madrid | Final de la Copa del Rey 2025
es.description:
Derrota en la prórroga de la final de la Copa del Rey. El Real Madrid, en una gran segunda mitad, dio la vuelta al tanto de Pedri en el 28’ con un lanzamiento de falta de Mbappé en el 70’ y un cabezazo de Tchouameni siete minutos más tarde. En el 84’ marcó Ferran Torres y llevó el encuentro a la prórroga, que decidió Koundé en el 116’ con un disparo desde la frontal.

ગાર્ડન ગાર્ડન થઈ જયુ દિલ એને ભાળી... (૨)

હો નોનુ મોઢુ ને નોની નથડી પેરી નાકે
નક્કી આ મેમાન મારા મલક ના લાગે
હો હો દુપટો આડો કરી ડોઢી નજરુ નાખે
સરમાળ સરમીલી છોડી છોનુ છોનુ તાકે
હો ગોરા ગોરા ગાલ ઉપરા ઝુલ્ફો નો છાયો
ભર બપોરે મને ચાંદલો દેખાયો... (૨)
હે આજે શેરી માં ઉતરી જોણે પરી
એને જોઈ આંખ થરી આ સુંદરી સે ચિયા ગોમના
આ રૂપ ની રોણી ચિયા ગોમના
મેમાન ચિયા ગોમના... (૨)

હો હો બોલી બોલે દેશી હાવ સાદી અને સિમ્પલ
હસતી હારી લાગે બન્ને ગાલે પડે ડિમ્પલ
હો હો ખભે રાખી પરશ આમથી તેંમ મારે ઓટા
મોઢુ મડી મડી આઇ ફોન માં પાડે ફોટા
હો આખી મહેફિલ માં એ એકજ રૂપાળી
ગાર્ડન ગાર્ડન થઈ જયુ દિલ એને ભાળી... (૨)
હે ઘેરો ઘાઘરો ને ચમકદાર ચોળી માથે ઓઢણી સે ધોળી
આ રૂપ ની રોણી ચિયા ગોમના... (3)

Phulera mein banne wala hain Bhandaar Ghar par kya har baar ki tarah iss baar bhi Banrakas ko hogi Pradhan ji ke iss kaam se dikkat? Ab Phulera mein hoga vikas ya Banrakas ek baar phir kahega alhua vikas? Jaanne ke liye Rashtriya Panchayati Raj Diwas par dekhiye Phulera Ka Panchayati Raj.

#TVF #Phulera #PanchayatiRaj 

Watch all parts of #PhuleraKaPanchayatiRaj here: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLTB0eCoUXErY5Jgt1VEjySYTaPde_w5oG&si=pwoMUSOFjMWWbkHS

This film, released on the occasion of National Panchayati Raj Day (राष्ट्रीय पंचायती राज दिवस; 24th April, 2025), highlights the importance of Own Sources of Revenue (OSR) in enabling Panchayati Raj Institutions (PRIs) to become self-reliant and better equipped to take up development works on their own.  It encourages Panchayats to adopt simple and effective ways to raise awareness among citizens about timely payment of Property Tax and other local taxes. These contributions directly support better service delivery, creation of public assets, and overall village development – making citizens active partners in the progress of their communities.  With the central message “जमा करके कर, बनाईये अपनी पंचायत को आत्मनिर्भर”, the film inspires collective efforts towards strengthening grassroots governance. The Ministry of Panchayati Raj remains committed to promoting OSR enhancement as a means to deepen decentralization and participatory rural development.

The Ministry of Panchayati Raj (MoPR), Government of India, is responsible for overseeing all matters related to Panchayati Raj and Panchayati Raj Institutions (PRIs) across the country. MoPR plays a pivotal role in promoting the decentralization process and strengthening rural local governance in States and Union Territories. For more information, visit the Ministry's official website: https://panchayat.gov.in

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

snippet.title: Adulting | S3E02 - Rat-Trap | Ft. Aisha & Yashaswini | Dice Media | Web Series
snippet.description:
Ray is reeling from disappointment after losing the project lead opportunity at work — and to make it worse, it went to the new guy, Abhinav. Struggling to focus, keep up with deadlines, and stay emotionally afloat, she starts to question her worth at the office.

Meanwhile, Nikhat is on a mission of her own: to finally make a move on Abeer. With Manav’s less-than-helpful guidance, things go sideways fast — and hilariously. From romantic misfires to workplace pressure, Adulting Season 3 continues to explore the chaos of ambition, heartbreak, and growing pains in your 20s.

Starring Aisha Ahmed, Yashaswini Dayama, Viraj Ghelani, and Rohan Khurana, Episode 2 brings more warmth, awkward laughs, and too-real emotions as Ray and Nikhat juggle friendship, failure, and flirtations — all while trying to keep it together in the middle of Mumbai.

snippet.title: NEW! Ep 4383 - Gogi ko Lag Chuki hai Satte ki Aadat? | Taarak Mehta ka Ooltah Chashmah | तारक मेहता
snippet.description:
Gokuldham Society | Gada Electronics | Bonus | Financial Year

Step into Jethalal’s world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun. Are you ready for the challenge? 

 Play now: https://gadaelectronics.page.link/dhgB  #GadaElectronics #TMKOCGame


Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Sachin Shroff / Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta
Sunayana Fozdar / Neha Mehta as Anjali Taarak Mehta
Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer
Munmun Dutta as Babita Krishnan Iyer
Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide
Sonalika Joshi as Madhvi Aatmaram Bhide
Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani / Khushi Mali as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi 
Ambika Ranjankar as Komal Hansraj Hathi
Kush Shah as Gulabkumar Hansraj Hathi (Goli)
Shyam Pathak as Popatlal Pandey
Sharad Sankla as Abdul
Azhar Shaikh as Pinku 
Ghanshyam Nayak / Kiran Bhatt as Nattu Kaka
Tanmay Vekaria as Bagha
Navina Wadekar / Monika Bhadoriya as Bawri

snippet.title: Chor Bazari Phir Se | Bhool Chuk Maaf | Rajkummar, Wamiqa | Pritam, Tanishk, Irshad, Neeraj, Sunidhi
snippet.description:
Chor bazaari do nainon kee,
Pehle thi aadat jo hat gayi!

Presenting the highly awaited ‘Chor Bazari Phir Se’ from ‘Bhool Chuk Maaf’, featuring Rajkummar Rao and Wamiqa Gabbi! Composed by Pritam and Tanishk Bagchi, it is sung by Neeraj Shridhar, Sunidhi Chauhan, Zahrah S Khan and Tanishk Bagchi. Penned by Irshad Kamil, it is perfect for all the Bollywood nostalgia lovers and those who love a good beat to dance on. Play it on loop, add it to your playlists, and get your groove on with ‘Chor Bazari Phir Se’!

#ChorBazari #PhirSe #RajkummarRao #WamiqaGabbi #Pritam #TanishkBagchi #IrshadKamil #NeerajShridhar #SunidhiChauhan #ZahrahSKhan #BhoolChukMaaf 

Title: Chor Bazari Phir Se
Singer: Neeraj Shridhar, Sunidhi Chauhan, Zahrah S Khan and Tanishk Bagchi 
Composers: Pritam and Tanishk Bagchi 
Music Production: Tanishk Bagchi & Ganesh Waghela
Lyricist: Irshad Kamil
Language: Hindi
Mix Master: Eric Pillai @ Future sound of Bombay
Assistant Mix Engineer: Michael Edwin Pillai
Original Music: Pritam
Director of Photography- Manu Anand
Director of Choreography- Vijay A Ganguly 
Costume Designer - Sheetal Iqbal Sharma 

Maddock Films presents #BhoolChukMaaf
In cinemas on 9th May
Cast - Rajkummar Rao, Wamiqa Gabbi, Sanjay Mishra, Seema Pahwa, Zakir Hussain, Raghubir Yadav, Ishtiyak Khan, Anubha Fatehpuria
Produced By: Dinesh Vijan 
Directed By: Karan Sharma 
Co-Producers: Sharada Karki Jalota 
Music By: Tanishk Bagchi 
Background Score: Ketan Sodha 
Story Screenplay & Dialogues By: Karan Sharma 
Director Of Photography: Sudeep Chatterjee 
Lyricist: Irshad Kamil
Costume Designer: Sheetal Iqbal Sharma
Associate Producer: Vineeta S Tanwar

Lyrics:
Chor bazaari do nainon kee pehle thi aadat jo hat gayi 
Pyaar kee jo teri-meri umr aayi thi vo katt gayi
Tu bhi tu hai main bhi main hoon duniyaan saaree dekh ulat gayi
Tu naa jaane main naa jaanoon kaise saaree baath palat gayi
Ghatni hi thi ye bhi ghatana ghatate-ghatate lo ye ghat gai
Haan chor bazaari do nainon kee pehle thi aadat jo hat gayi

Jhoomariya jhoomariya manwa
Ban baagi sa
Jhoomariya jhoomariya tanwa
Bedaagi
Man mera dhad dhad dhad dhadkaaye
Koi na phir sar sar sar chadh jaaye
Kasam se baazi haath na apne aaye
Nain agar lad jaayein

Taareef teri karnaa tuje khone se darana
Haan bhool gaya ab tujh pe din mein chaar dafa maranaa

Taareef teri karnaa tuje khone se darana
Haan bhool gaya ab tujh pe din mein chaar dafa maranaa

Laaj-sharam kee choti-moti jo thi dori vo bhi katt gayi
Chowk-chaubaare gali-mohalle khol ke main saare ghunghat gayi
Ek hue the do se donon donon kee ab raahen bant gayi
Haan chor bazaari do nainon kee pehle thi aadat jo hat gayi

Bade hi nain ladaake se
Lade the roz baazaaron mein
Kisi ko dhoond hi lete the
Sadak pe roz hazaaron mein
Bahas nahin kam kam kam karte
Na ab yeh gham gham gham karte
Badal gaye dheere dheere do naina
Mera kya kya kya kehna

Haan chor bazaari do nainon kee pehle thi aadat jo hat gayi
Haan rang-birangaa paani pee ke sidhi-saadi kudi bighad gayi

LOVE !! LIKE !! COMMENTS !! SUBSCRIBE

Song Lyrics In Hindi 

अरे भीड़ पाड़ दया भीड़ के मह त fair घुमा दया सा 
कोए आबल टीटी पाके उसपे tair चड़ा दया सा 
पाप और पुन का बनया रहवे यो कॉम्बिनेशन सा 
मार क मानस गंगा कानी गेर घुमा दया सा 
हम अपनी धुन म जीते , संग के सारे बालक चीते  जो मरण मारण न तयार रहवे वो टोला रह है 

माहरा ठाडे गैल्या रोला रह स 
चा की गैल्या तोला रह स 
स्याना गैल्या बनती कौनया 
दिल म बाबा भोला रह स

कर के पंगे चौथे दिन हम जेल बी जा ल्या सा 
किसे जानकार प 2 दिन भीतर बेल करा ल्या सा 
जे गोली लागे पड़े रहवा सा जाके जंगला म 
जे चाकू छीनी लागे काला तेल लगा ल्या सा 
बैठे शूटर माह रे साथ बी kp kundu deep 
लाठ बी जिनका भरया खून त घर का कोला कोला रह स

हम करा ज़ाब्ता रसिया का समान मंगाके न 
लागे माथे के म मारे बंदा परे बगाके न 
जो अपने मन म एंडी हमने वेहे पेले है 
अरे रेहड़ी कौनया लूटी झूठी धोंस दिखाके न्न 
घुमा बनके न हम काल , र दोनू आँख रह वे स
 लाल र गैल्या धरया टूल म प्योर भाग का गोला रह स 

Song Lyrics In English

are bheed paad daya bheed me badke fair guma dya sa 
koe abal titi paake usape tair chada daya sa 
makha paap aur puny ka banaaya rahave yo kombineshan sa 
maar ka maanas ganga kaanee ger guma daya sa 
re ham apanee dhunen ma jeete, gelya saare baalak cheete jo maran maran na tayaar rahave vo tola rah sai 

mhaara thaade galiya rola rah sa 
cha kee galiya tola rah sa 
syaana gailya banti kaunaya 
dil maan baaba bhola rah sa

re ham kara jaabta rasiya ka samaan mangaake na 
laage maathe ke me maare banda pare baagaake na 
jo apane man ma endee hamne vohe pele sai 
are rehadee kaunaya lootee jhoothi dhons dikhke ne
re haande banake na ham kaal, aar donoo aankh rav se laal gelya dharya tool me pyor bhaag ka gola rah se

kar ke pange chauthe din ham jel bee ja lya sa 
kisase jaankaar pe 2 din bhitar bel karalya sa 
je gol laage pade rahava sa jaake jangala ma 
je chaakoo cheenee laage kaala tel laga le sa 
re baithe shooter maah re saath  bgi  kp bintu deep laath bee jinka bharaaya khoon ta ghar ka kola kola rah se

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

snippet.description:
सचिन टिचकुले एक महत्वाकांक्षी ठेकेदार है जिसे घर और कार्यस्थल दोनों जगह हर किसी के विरोध का सामना करना पड़ता है। लेकिन वह संघर्ष करना जारी रखता है जबकि उसके परिवार के सदस्य गलत तरीके से कमाए गए पैसे को हड़पने में लगे रहते हैं।

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.
